doc.after: The Turks and Caicos Islands are a biodiversity hotspot The islands have many endemic species and others of international importance due to the conditions created by the oldest established salt pan development in the Caribbean The variety of species includes a number of endemic species of lizards snakes insects and plants and marine organisms in addition to being an important breeding area for seabirds 65
